<TD valign=top>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
&lt;sirmorte&gt;
</FONT></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I was reading about Harmony, and strangly enough, it isn't clear how to use the spell. Should I cast it on me, on one monsters, on several monsters or since it is an area effect, get near several monsters and cast on me or them. Frankly, getting near several mobs doesn't sound right since I am not a malee character.<BR> Can anyone specify how this spell is to be used? Thanks.</FONT>
</TD></TR>

<TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7">
<TD valign=top>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
&lt;Kamile&gt;
</FONT></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Harmony is used for pulling from static spawn points.  Assuming you are low level...go to a camp site such as the dervs, orcs, goblins, any site that has multiple guys just standing around.  Now, standing away from the camp, cast harmony.<P>I personally cast it on every mob to make sure I got them all, but it is AE and this is only a safety precaution.<P>Now that the whole camp is harmonied, you can safely pull singles (whether with a bow, spell or running up there quickly) from the camp.  However, you have to be sure you pull the mob away cause otherwise when harmony runs out you will be in trouble.<P>Harmony can also be used in places like City of Mist if you just want to run past guys without fighting them.<P>Note however that the mob has to stay put.  Harmony will not work on wandering mobs!<P>I think that about covers it.   <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"></FONT>
</TD></TR>

<TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF">
<TD valign=top>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Wolfkind
</FONT></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">If you want to see the true power of harmony go to the east commons tunnel (or wherever the main trading loc is on your server) and cast it on someone in the middle of a large group for a truly awesome lightshow.</FONT>
</TD></TR>

<TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7">
<TD valign=top>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Lasiel
</FONT></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Harmony is also good to cast on ones self in certain situations.<BR>Sisters camp in LFay for example. I camped there solo from lev 9-14. Walk onto the fire in the camp and cast on yourself. Since it's AoE, you have just harmonied 3 of the 4 sisters, leaving the last one as an easy pull. You have to be careful that you pull them so that one does not come close to another, or you get an extra sister or 2 as well. This also saves you mana by only having to cast on 1 rather than 4 (all that extra mana for nuking).</FONT>
</TD></TR>

<TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF">
<TD valign=top>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Gurk
</FONT></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Thats odd, Harmony would not work for me in CoM... I was even told by others it doesnt work in that zone. I cast it on a few NPCs and they still agroed on me.<P>Something else to add, once a mob has the harmony effect on them, they can still be agroed by touch. If you or the mob you are pulling touch another NPC, harmony will break. It will even work on wondering NPCs. Before a recent patch if you were too far away you saw no spell effect at all. Now from any distance you can see the effect land on the target but not the NPCs around them. If you get near then you will see all the NPCs it affects.<P>So in an outdoor zone a druid can single pull any NPC they want with some skill and timing. It really is a great spell, take some time to master it. I think it makes druids better puller then monks because they can get NPCs deeper into a spawn then the first ones they enounter. An exsample... I am able to single pull the Ry'Gorr chief, or Blacksmith(I really want that hammer) from a full spawn, with little or no trouble.</FONT>
</TD></TR>

